NAME
	alert-watcher (service) - poll a signal file and a status file and emit a sequential alert file per qualifying line or status change

INTERFACE
	service (MatrixService)

READS
	signals			one signal per line, whitespace fields:
				id asset direction confidence signal_type timestamp
	portfolio/defense/status	single status token

WRITES
	alert-0000, alert-0001, ...	one plain-text message per file:
				"high-confidence signal: <asset> <dir> <stype> (conf=<conf>)"
				or "defense status changed: <old> -> <new>"

DESCRIPTION
	Polls every 5000 ms.  A signal qualifies when its confidence
	field is >= "0.7" by string comparison.  The alert counter is
	in-memory: it resets on reload, and qualifying signals re-emit
	every poll (no dedup) - consumers should treat the outdir as a
	stream to drain, not a set.  The first status read primes the
	comparison; changes alert from the second poll on.

SEE ALSO
	signal-feed (renders the same signals file)
